HEADWORD: Unused
<hw>Un*used"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not used;
<as>as, an <ex>unused</ex> book; an <ex>unused</ex>
apartment</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not habituated; unaccustomed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Unused</qex> to bend, impatient of control.</q>
<rj><qau>Thomson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unusual</ent>⟦br⟧
